# Database and Data Protection

Do not take any action that would delete the database or any data already stored in it.

## Prohibited Actions

- Do not run commands or migrations that drop the database, reset the schema, or truncate/delete tables
- Do not suggest or execute `prisma migrate reset`, `db push --force-reset`, or equivalent destructive operations on production or shared data
- Do not write or run code that deletes, truncates, or clears existing records unless the user explicitly requests data removal for a specific purpose
- Do not remove or alter migrations or schema in ways that would require wiping and recreating the database

## Allowed

- Adding new tables, columns, or migrations that extend the schema without removing existing data
- Read-only queries and reporting
- The user may explicitly ask to reset or clear data; only then consider destructive operations, and confirm before proceeding
